"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"21d159",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Transcribing"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e67c47",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Use computerized physician order entry to eliminate handwriting errors"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-3 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ab5bb8",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Dispensing"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a80af9",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Have clinical pharmacists oversee the medication dispensing process"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7ba19d",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Use “tall man” lettering and other strategies to minimize confusion between look-alike, sound-alike medications. Starting on the left side of a drug name, tall man lettering highlights the differences between similar drug names by capitalizing dissimilar letters (e.g., ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"DOP"
]
},
"amine and ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"DOBUT"
]
},
"amine)"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-4 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7258e7",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Administration"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"697d00",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Adhere to the “five rights” of administering medication safely (administering the right medication, in the right dose, at the right time, by the right route, to the right patient)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9c3778",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Use barcode medication administration to ensure medications are given to the correct patient"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d03f43",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Minimize interruptions to allow nurses to administer medications safely"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f460a2",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Use smart infusion pumps for intravenous infusions"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"86603f",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Use patient education and revised medication labels to improve patient comprehension of administration instructions"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
}
